# SynapseOS — Cline/Kilo Code Rules

## What You're Building
SynapseOS: BYOK RAG platform on Oracle ARM (4 vCPU / 24GB RAM, NO GPU).
Two endpoints: /v1/query (fast RAG ~235ms) and /v1/think (cognitive engine ~865ms).

## Locked Stack
FastAPI 0.115 | Qdrant 1.13.5 | fastembed BAAI/bge-base-en-v1.5 |
LiteLLM (Groq primary) | mem0ai | Crawl4AI | Docling |
RAGAS 0.2.15 | DSPy 2.5.20 | Langfuse v3 | KeyDB | MinIO | FastMCP

## Hard ARM Rules
OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 | batch_size=64 ingest / 16 query |
rerank max 15 docs | KeyDB AOF only no RDB |
Qdrant on_disk=True | Docling concurrency=1

## Code Standards
- Always async/await
- Full files — no truncation
- All secrets via os.environ
- tenant_id filter on all Qdrant queries
- Fernet AES-256 for BYOK key storage

## File Map
src/api/ → routes + middleware
src/core/ → retrieval, generation, ingestion
src/cognitive/ → engine, memory, tools, reflection, planner
sdk/ → Python + TypeScript clients
mcp/ → FastMCP server
cloudflare/ → Workers edge proxy
